Hypothetical logs aside, and stun/contact procs aside, i'll tell you another reason why CA &gt; CS.<br>
<br>
Fact is that CA reduces the number of times you are hit, period.  Fact also is that CS neither reduces the maximum hit of the mob, nor the minimum hit.  You will still take max damage hits and you can never mitigate it below minimum damage hits.  In this respect, CS is far less useful for it's 10% of the time than getting missed 10% more.<br>
<br>
Ya, CS may reduce the damage you take, but it can only reduce it to a specific number, and will not totally eliminate damage.  CA will.  CA &gt; CS, end of discussion. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
